   Factory that creates Session objects
   Key Characteristics: Heavy-weight object ⚠️, Created once per application and Thread-safe ✅
   Holds: DB configuration ,Mapping metadata and 2nd level cache
        SessionFactory factory = new Configuration()
            .configure()
            .buildSessionFactory();
  ✔ Responsibilities: Create sessions, Maintain cache and Store ORM mappings

  What is Session?
    Connection between application and database
    Key Characteristics: Light-weight object, Created per request/transaction and NOT thread-safe ❌ and Represents persistence context
    Session session = factory.openSession();
    
    User user = session.get(User.class, 1);
    ✔ Responsibilities: CRUD operations, Manage entity lifecycle, First-level cache and Dirty checking
